[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (1) **Multi-asset clinical-policy-as-code governance scaffolding (therapeutic-content-corpus, crisis-screening-classifier, FDA-strategy-artifact, consent-language, mandatory-reporting-routing-policy, companion-pattern-detection-policy) underspecified despite explicit prose elevation.** The recipe correctly elevates therapeutic-content-corpus-as-versioned-governance-artifact-with-behavioral-health-clinical-leadership-signature-as-launch-gate, crisis-screening-classifier-with-held-out-validation-corpus-and-false-negative-rate-as-launch-gate, FDA-strategy-artifact-as-regulatory-counsel-reviewed-versioned-asset, consent-language-as-clinical-leadership-and-legal-counsel-reviewed-versioned-asset (with state-specific variations), mandatory-reporting-routing-policy-as-per-state-and-per-disclosure-class-versioned-asset, and companion-pattern-detection-policy-as-behavioral-health-clinical-leadership-reviewed-versioned-asset in multiple separate places. Despite this thorough prose elevation (the recipe is explicit about these primitives in the General Architecture cross-cutting design points subsection plus the Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready subsection plus the Honest Take), the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode treat the multi-asset governance as institutional-policy reference rather than as architectural primitives with explicit version-control discipline, sandbox testing against held-out mental-health-support cases, staged rollout with per-asset canary, rollback-on-regression, named ownership at the behavioral-health-clinical-leadership plus the licensed-clinician-workforce operations plus compliance plus regulatory team, per-asset-version stamping on every support-decision-record, annual review cadence, and the appropriate specialty-society liaison (American Psychiatric Association, American Psychological Association). Recipe-acute amplification because the bot is the chapter's first life-safety-acute recipe and the bot's clinical safety floor is bounded above by all six artifacts simultaneously, and because the bot approaches the FDA SaMD line with active regulatory exposure. The recipe contains an explicit `<!-- TODO (TechWriter): Expert review S1 (HIGH). Promote therapeutic-content-corpus-as-code lifecycle to architectural primitive ... Extend to crisis-screening-classifier, FDA-strategy-artifact, consent-language, and mandatory-reporting-routing-policy as parallel versioned governance assets. -->` marker anticipating this finding.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (2) **Sensitive-disclosure store, crisis-event record, longitudinal store, support-decision-record journal, and tool-call ledger accumulate multi-year-longitudinal mental-health-PHI-rich free-text outside archive-reference pattern, with recipe-distinct mental-health-PHI-as-clinical-record-of-elevated-sensitivity and 42-CFR-Part-2-applicability-where-substance-use-treatment-data-is-involved and state-specific-mental-health-record-retention-floors-often-exceeding-general-medical-record-rules and FDA-SaMD-post-market-obligations and litigation-hold-obligations amplifications.** Same chapter pattern as 11.4 through 11.7 with recipe-distinct mental-health-extensions. The Step 6 persist_support_artifacts decision-record write includes the full decision_payload, full citations, full active-version stamps. The Step 6C sensitive_disclosure_store write captures full disclosure_excerpt and mandatory_reporting_relevance. The Step 3 crisis_event_record write captures full crisis_dimensions, urgency, screening_result. The longitudinal-store updates accumulate disclosures, symptom-tracking, and mental-health context across years; the tool-call-ledger writes for therapeutic_content_retrieve, safety_plan_retrieve, symptom_tracking_retrieve, symptom_log_record, clinical_rule_compute, conversation_history_retrieve, crisis_resource_retrieve, warm_handoff_propose, care_team_alert_propose, mandatory_report_route, longitudinal_disclosure_record include the full retrieved member-specific data and full structured tool results. The recipe-distinct dimensions include the sensitive-disclosure-surface-as-separately-keyed-with-separately-restricted-access framing (the recipe's own prose: "Sensitive-disclosure store and crisis-event record use separate KMS keys and separate access-control surfaces"), the per-record-class retention floor reconciliation covering the longest of HIPAA's six-year minimum, state-specific mental-health-record retention rule