[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **The therapeutic-content library is a per-modality and per-content-item versioned governance artifact owned by behavioral-health clinical leadership, with each piece of content having a defined indication and contraindication, an effective date, and an annual review schedule.** The architecture should specify the version-control discipline (per-content-item semantic versioning, sandbox testing against held-out support cases covering both common and atypical presentations per condition and per modality, staged rollout with per-content canary, rollback-on-regression, named ownership at the behavioral-health-clinical-leadership plus the licensed-clinician-workforce operations plus compliance plus regulatory team plus the appropriate specialty-society liaison), the per-content change-management process (a change to the CBT-for-anxiety content goes through the behavioral-health-clinical-leadership plus the licensed-clinician-workforce operations plus compliance), the per-content-version-stamping on every support-decision-record (already partial credit at Step 6; promote to architectural primitive across all support-decision types including therapeutic-content-delivery, psychoeducation-delivery, and safety-plan-step-surfacing), the annual review cadence with behavioral-health-clinical-leadership re-sign-off, and the behavioral-health-clinical-leadership-signature-as-launch-gate workflow per content item.
