[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The crisis-screening classifier is a separately-governed versioned asset with held-out validation corpus and false-negative-rate as launch-gate metric.** The architecture should specify the per-classifier-version validation (held-out corpus curated by licensed mental-health clinicians, including crisis-language variants by language, by demographic cohort, by condition, and by adversarial-test scenarios), the per-cohort calibration (linguistic and cultural variations in crisis expression), the per-classifier-version-stamping on every crisis-event-record (already partial credit at Step 3 `active_classifier_version: CRISIS_CLASSIFIER_VERSION`), the false-negative-rate as launch-gate metric with explicit threshold (target less than 2%, ideally under 1% for high-risk dimensions including active suicidal ideation with plan and means and intent), and the change-management process owned jointly by behavioral-health clinical leadership, the licensed-clinician-workforce operations team, and the data-science team.
