[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The consent language is a clinical-leadership-and-legal-counsel-reviewed versioned asset with state-specific variations.** The architecture should specify the per-state-and-per-language-variations of the consent language (mental-health-record privacy law variations by state, plus 42 CFR Part 2 substance-use treatment-data variations where applicable), the per-version review by behavioral-health-clinical-leadership and legal counsel familiar with state-specific mental-health-record statutes, the per-version-stamping on every consent record (already partial credit at Step 1B `consent_record.consent_version = state_specific_consent.version`), and the change-management process owned jointly by legal counsel and behavioral-health-clinical-leadership.
